Plot:

Body of Review: As Red Light District continues to try producing feature porn as a sideline to their extremely popular gonzo, they have found an appreciative audience. I suspect that will always be the case as long as they keep a lot of hardcore sex inside the movies and make the movies appealing to the mind as well as the crotch. Such was the case with Sex Pix, the second of three initial efforts but director James Avalon that started with Darkside. To quote a famous songstress, "I don't like flashbacks in movies; I like the story to proceedâ€¦" I was hesitant when first watching the movie to get into it but it literally sucked me in as I watched with a growing enthusiasm. The sex was on par with the usual Red Light District but the complex nature of the story was good as mental floss too. Rather than bounce around from present to past, it handled scenes in reverse order in a linear fashion. This made it easier to keep track of the story while providing some heated sex along the way.
